Imagine you just called time(2) and got a time_t value. Something like:<p><pre><code>    time_t asdf = time();
</code></pre>
And now you want to use printf to print that value to the screen. You can cast to &#x27;long long&#x27;, which is guaranteed to be at at least 64 bits wide, and ensure no loss of precision occurs:<p><pre><code>    printf(&quot;%lld&quot;, (long long)asdf);
</code></pre>
That will work whether time_t is 32 bit or 64 bit.

